Abstract: Service staffs of the rich will have to expand in 21st century, perhaps adding a techster, medster, monetician and ecotist to the maid, launderer, chef, chauffeur and nanny; drawing (M)
Snippet: Service staffs of the rich will have to expand in 21st century, perhaps adding a techster, medster, monetician and ecotist to the maid, launderer, chef, chauffeur and nanny; drawing (M)
LeadParagraph: IN the swelling ranks of the superwealthy, where the number of American families worth more than $10 million has jumped fourfold, to 275,000, over the last decade, demand for servants has risen to levels not seen since the Roaring Twenties, before household appliances brought factory-floor efficiency to the home.
